        "title": "Sacred Geometry in Three Dimensions",
        "paragraphs": [
            "Borobudur is not merely a temple—it's a three-dimensional mandala, a cosmic diagram that guides pilgrims from earthly desire to enlightenment. Built in the 9th century, its nine stacked platforms represent the Buddhist cosmology's layers of existence.",
            "Our miniature preserves the monument's sacred mathematics: six square platforms crowned by three circular ones, culminating in a central stupa that reaches toward the sky. Each of the 72 perforated stupas contains a Buddha statue, visible through diamond-shaped openings.",
